.TH BCA-DIFF 1  "big-code-analysis 1.1.0" "big-code-analysis Manual"
.SH NAME
bca\-diff \- Compare two metric\-output runs and report, per metric, which files changed (old to new), plus files added/removed between the two sets. Each side is a per\-file JSON file or a directory tree of them (the form `bca metrics \-O json \-\-output DIR` writes). Replaces the grammar\-bump glue chain — the external `json\-minimal\-tests` binary plus `split\-minimal\-tests.py` — with one native command. Always exits 0 on success; the diff is informational, not a gate
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBbca\-diff\fR [\fB\-\-format\fR] [\fB\-\-min\-change\fR] [\fB\-\-metric\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIOLD\fR> <\fINEW\fR> 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Compare two metric\-output runs and report, per metric, which files changed (old to new), plus files added/removed between the two sets. Each side is a per\-file JSON file or a directory tree of them (the form `bca metrics \-O json \-\-output DIR` writes). Replaces the grammar\-bump glue chain — the external `json\-minimal\-tests` binary plus `split\-minimal\-tests.py` — with one native command. Always exits 0 on success; the diff is informational, not a gate
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-format\fR \fI<FORMAT>\fR [default: tty]
Output style: `tty` (default), `markdown`, or `json`
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
tty
.IP \(bu 2
markdown
.IP \(bu 2
json
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-min\-change\fR \fI<MIN_CHANGE>\fR [default: 0]
Minimum absolute change for a per\-file metric delta to be reported. `0` (the default) reports any change. Mirrors `split\-minimal\-tests.py`\*(Aqs `\-t` threshold
.TP
\fB\-\-metric\fR \fI<METRIC>\fR
Restrict the diff to one or more metrics (repeatable). Names are those printed by `bca list\-metrics` (e.g. `cyclomatic`, `sloc`). When omitted, every metric is reported
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
<\fIOLD\fR>
Old (base) metric output — the "before" side. A per\-file JSON file or a directory of per\-file JSON
.TP
<\fINEW\fR>
New (updated) metric output — the "after" side. A per\-file JSON file or a directory of per\-file JSON
